nuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}} ({{ill|User talk:Immanuelle|de|User talk:Immanuelle|ja|User talk:Immanuelle|zh|User talk:Immanuelle|lt=Immanuelle|lt_ja=Immanuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}}) 09:48, 26 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=Switching over to deprecating the templates. So things might be a bit unexpected. {{ill|User:Immanuelle|de|User:Immanuelle|ja|User:Immanuelle|zh|User:Immanuelle|lt=Immanuelle|lt_ja=Immanuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}} ({{ill|User talk:Immanuelle|de|User talk:Immanuelle|ja|User talk:Immanuelle|zh|User talk:Immanuelle|lt=Immanuelle|lt_ja=Immanuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}}) 05:01, 18 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=If this is in the format "List of Shikinaisha in X" then I have linked all existing shrines into the table. Otherwise I have not. Translation of the texts will come later as it is a lot less difficult than the tables. Exception if there is another comment explaining the exception below {{ill|User:Immanuelle|de|User:Immanuelle|ja|User:Immanuelle|zh|User:Immanuelle|lt=Immanuelle|lt_ja=Immanuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}} ({{ill|User talk:Immanuelle|de|User talk:Immanuelle|ja|User talk:Immanuelle|zh|User talk:Immanuelle|lt=Immanuelle|lt_ja=Immanuelle|lt_de=Immanuelle|lt_zh=Immanuelle}}) 05:34, 17 March 2025 (UTC)}} '''{{ill|List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province|de|List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国の式内社一覧|zh|List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province|lt=List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province|lt_ja=しもうさのくにのしきないしゃいちらん|lt_de=List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province|lt_zh=List of Shikinaisha in Shimōsa Province}}''' (下総国の式内社一覧) This is a list of shrines recorded in the volumes 9 and 10 of the ''Engishiki'' “Jinmyōchō (Upper and Lower)” ({{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|de|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|zh|Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}) – namely, the so‑called {{ill|Shikinaisha|de|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|zh|Shikinaisha}} and their {{ill|candidate shrines|de|candidate shrines|ja|論社|zh|candidate shrines}} – that are classified as part of Shimōsa Province.
It also includes, as an addendum, shrines that existed at the time the ''Engishiki'' Jinmyōchō was compiled but are not recorded in it, the so‑called {{ill|Shikigaisha|de|Shikigaisha|ja|式外社|zh|Shikigaisha}}.
== Shikinaisha == In the ''Engishiki'' Jinmyōchō, a total of 11 shrines are recorded – one major shrine (Myojin Taisha) and ten minor shrines (Shosha).
