in the volumes 9 and 10 of the ''Engishiki'' “Jinmyōchō (Upper and Lower)” ({{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|de|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|zh|Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}) – namely, the so‑called {{ill|Shikinaisha|de|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|zh|Shikinaisha}} and their {{ill|candidate shrines|de|candidate shrines|ja|論社|zh|candidate shrines}} – that are classified as part of Shimōsa Province.
It also includes, as an addendum, shrines that existed at the time the ''Engishiki'' Jinmyōchō was compiled but are not recorded in it, the so‑called {{ill|Shikigaisha|de|Shikigaisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|zh|Shikigaisha}}.
